<br>
Black pledge of allegiance- in the original post it was edited and I don't really feel like hunting down the school's website. I don't think I want to trade places with the &quot;white&quot; teacher if the sample is indicative of the source material. Saying a seperate pledge IS divisive and not the same as having a flag displayed.<br>
<br>
Someone said their ancestors were allowed to hang their flag since they came to this country. I'm curious what flag that was, you might consider reading a bit about living conditions and ethnic tensions in New York City at the turn of the last century.<br>
<br>
One person said, or implied, that they were tired of hearing about Native American discrimination and another wanted to know why people are still going on about the Holocaust. Both of these were instances of genocide and have been either suppressed, denied, or come under attack by revisionists.<br>
<br>
I don't remember ever hearing anyone claiming slavery never existed in this country. I don't remember hearing anyone questioning the number of slaves that were kept or shipped over. And I doubt that wide-spread killing of slaves took place, certainly not with the intent of removing them from the planet.<br>
<br>
Slaves were not the only ones to suffer in the class structure of 19th century America. Not every low income, non-slave joined groups such as the &quot;Patrollers&quot; and the &quot;Klan&quot;. Those who did passed their hatred and anger on to many of their descendants, and &quot;blacks&quot; were not their only victims. It is people who harbor like feelings that are responsible for much of the discrimination in our country. <br>
<br>
Before anyone purposely misunderstands what I'm saying, I don't deny slaves were beaten and killed. I am only saying genocide was not the intent. All of these things are a part of our Nation's past that we cannot afford to forget or ignore.<br>
<br>
As for reparation, there is no way to make it equitable. As long as people desire to be compensated for past damages suffered by their ancestors, they will continue to feel victimized. <p>Cattundanser Whitefang<BR>
Rogue of the Tribunal<BR>
